# LocalMoney Solana - Localnet Deployment Guide

## Overview
LocalMoney uses **localnet only** for development and testing. No mainnet or devnet deployments should be performed.

## Quick Start Commands

### Start Local Validator
```bash
# Start local test validator with required programs
anchor run start-local

# Alternative: Start with specific options
solana-test-validator --reset --quiet \
  --bpf-program TokenkegQfeZyiNwAJbNbGKPFXCWuBvf9Ss623VQ5DA BPFLoader2111111111111111111111111111111111 \
  --clone metaqbxxUerdq28cj1RbAWkYQm3ybzjb6a8bt518x1s
```

### Build and Deploy
```bash
# Build all programs
anchor build

# Deploy to localnet (only allowed deployment target)
anchor deploy --provider.cluster localnet

# Run tests on localnet
anchor test --skip-local-validator
# OR use the script
yarn run local-test
```

## Configuration Files

### Anchor Configuration
Main config: [Anchor.toml](mdc:Anchor.toml)
- **Provider cluster**: Always set to `localnet`
- **Wallet**: Uses `~/.config/solana/id.json`
- **Programs**: All 5 programs configured for localnet only

